## Objective: Break down requirements into milestones, modules, interfaces, data models, and release plans.

## Applicable to: New project launches, refactoring, and roadmap reviews.

## Input: Requirements documentation, business objectives, constraints (time/human resources/budget/compliance).

## Output: /docs/PLAN.md, module diagram (Mermaid), milestones, and acceptance criteria.

## Example Usage
```
/PLAN 为 {{PROJECT}} 制定 4 周 MVP 计划。重点：{{FEATURE}}。约束：单人开发、优先 iOS/Android+Web 可用。
```
## Template Output Structure
- /docs/PLAN.md
- /docs/ARCHITECTURE.md (includes Web/Native/Weixin layer, Edge/Server - - - layer, DB/Vector/Authentication layer, CI/CD)
- /docs/APIs.md (API list, response examples)
- /docs/SCOPES.md (MVP/Next/Backlog)
- Mermaid Architecture Diagrams and Sequence Diagrams

## Example Highlights
- Milestones: W1 Skeleton, W2 Data/Backend, W3 Frontend Integration 
- Testing, W4 Testing and Release
- Risks and Alternative Solutions (e.g., WeChat capability limitations, iOS review special items)
- Translated with DeepL.com (free version)